 {"id":"beads_rust-rdrp","title":"BUG: NOT NULL constraint fails on optional fields during insert","description":"# BUG: NOT NULL constraint fails on optional fields during insert

## Symptom
All E2E tests fail with:
```
Database error: NOT NULL constraint failed: issues.description
```

## Root Cause
Schema has: `description TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''`
But INSERT statement passes `issue.description` directly as `Option<String>`.
When `None`, SQLite receives NULL which violates NOT NULL constraint.

## Fix
Convert `None` to empty string before INSERT for all `NOT NULL DEFAULT ''` fields:
- description
- design
- acceptance_criteria
- notes
- owner
- created_by
- close_reason
- closed_by_session
- source_system
- deleted_by
- delete_reason
- original_type
- sender

## Location
src/storage/sqlite.rs lines 193-230 (insert_issue function)","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-17T14:39:37.812410166Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-17T15:18:44.918596194Z","closed_at":"2026-01-17T15:18:44.918596194Z","close_reason":"Fixed NOT NULL constraint bug: update_issue now converts None to empty string for NOT NULL DEFAULT '' fields, and issue_from_row converts empty strings back to None for API consistency. All storage_crud and conformance tests pass.","compaction_level":0}
